"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"After closing the figure with plt.close() on line 11, there is no active figure. Therefore, when trying to get the active figure with get_active_figure() on line 13, it will return None. However, the code then tries to add a text label to the axes of the closed figure on line 18, which will result in an error because the figure is already closed.\",\n  \"patch\": \"11c11\\n< plt.close()\\n---\\n> # Remove this line to keep the figure open\\n\\n18c18\\n< ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n---\\n> ac_fig.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\") doesn't work because ac_fig is None. Instead, you should add the text before closing the figure.\\n\\nThe corrected code would be:\\n\\n1 import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n2 \\n3 def get_active_figure():\\n4     fig_stack = plt.get_fignums()\\n5     if len(fig_stack) == 0:\\n6         return None\\n7     return plt.gcf()\\n8 \\n9 fig, ax = plt.subplots()\\n10 ax.plot([0, 1, 2, 3], [0, 4, 5, 6])\\n11 ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n12 plt.show(block=False)\\n13 plt.close()\\n\"\n}"